---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="EduPath · AI-Driven Learning Platform" description="EduPath uses LLMs to generate personalised learning curricula that adapt to each learner.">
  <div class="bg-slate-950 min-h-screen">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-32 pb-24">

    <a href="/projects" class="text-sm text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8 inline-block">← All projects</a>

    <div class="mb-2">
      <span class="text-xs font-medium text-amber-400 bg-amber-950/50 rounded px-2.5 py-1">Building</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-2">EduPath</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 mb-10">AI-driven personalised learning platform.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-emerald-500 bg-slate-900/60 p-6">
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          "Learning should adapt to you. Not the other way around."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Traditional learning is expensive, rigid, and one-size-fits-all. Masters programmes cost tens of thousands. Online courses don't adapt. The result: people either overpay for structure they don't need, or get lost in a sea of content with no clear path.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">How it works</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">EduPath uses LLMs to generate personalised learning programmes from scratch. The input is simple: your goal and your starting point. The output is a structured, actionable path built around you.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {[
            "Fully personalised curriculum based on specific goals and current knowledge level",
            "Dynamic structure that evolves as you progress and your needs change",
            "Ability to go deep into specific topics or skip what's already known",
            "Combines courses, articles, videos and other formats into a single coherent path",
            "High-quality learning at a fraction of the cost of traditional programmes",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-emerald-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▸</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Where we are</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          First version built, tested and validated with real learners. The initial use case has been delivered and iterated on based on real feedback. Now evolving from a specific implementation into a more scalable and repeatable system.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl">Real output — Sports Nursing programme</h2>
          <a href="/demos/edupath-programa-enfermeria.html" target="_blank"
             class="text-xs text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors flex items-center gap-1 shrink-0 ml-4">
            Open full
            <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mb-4">A full learning programme generated by EduPath — from scratch, personalised to a real learner's goals.</p>
        <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-white/8">
          <div class="bg-slate-800 px-4 py-2.5 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="flex gap-1.5">
              <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/70"></div>
              <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/70"></div>
              <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-green-500/70"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="flex-1 bg-slate-700/60 rounded px-3 py-0.5 text-xs text-slate-400 font-mono text-center truncate">EduPath · Programa de Enfermería Deportiva</span>
          </div>
          <iframe
            src="/demos/edupath-programa-enfermeria.html"
            class="w-full border-0 block"
            style="height: 520px;"
            loading="lazy"
            title="EduPath — Sports Nursing Programme"
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Key learnings</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          {[
            "Structure matters as much as content: a well-ordered path is half the work",
            "AI adds real value in personalisation, not just content generation",
            "Users need direction more than they need options",
            "Iterating based on actual usage reveals things no planning session will",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-slate-400">
              <span class="text-slate-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0">·</span>
              <span>{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {["EdTech", "LLM", "Product", "React", "Personalisation"].map(tag => (
        <span class="text-xs text-blue-400 bg-blue-950/40 rounded px-2 py-0.5">{tag}</span>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
